\begin_layout Section
Discussion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
First, discuss the magnitudes & values of our calculated diffusion coefficients
 compared to literature (Lobnig, Sabioni) and simulations (Vaari).
 Explicitly say why they agree or don't.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
VERY CLEARLY explain why Vaari's total 3D diffusion coefficients differ
 so much from ours in magnitude.
 Did he use a different potential? Different parameters? Why is it so different?
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Explicitly state which direction (in-plane or out-of-plane) is slower, and
 by how much.
 This is the direction that we want to induce for slower corrosion rates.
 Compare this difference in diffusivity with the corrosion rate differences
 in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Shahryari2009,RaviKumar2005"

\end_inset

 for the most direct comparison.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Mention how some studies show grain boundary diffusion to be 1,000x times
 faster than the effective diffusivity 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Sabioni2005"

\end_inset

, though controversy still exists whether it's bulk or GB dominated transport
 [WE SHOULD FIND MORE LITERATURE DISCUSSING THIS]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Talk about what should be done to confirm whether this effect is real, and
 
\emph on
utilizable.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Need explicit measurements of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{Cr_{2}O_{3}}$
\end_inset

 texture via EBSD as a function of processing (cast, annealed, rolled, forged,
 SPD)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Need explicit measurements of tracer diffusion rates in differently oriented
 single crystals of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{Cr_{2}O_{3}}$
\end_inset

 to confirm our measurements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Need to try actual corrosion experiments on as-manufactured materials by
 different processes to confirm
\end_layout

\end_deeper
